  "text": "We created two other Boolean models based on more recent papers, published in 2001 and 2004 [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] , shown in Figure 2 . Another hazard occurs when Slp1 is 1 and Cdc2 is 1. Then either Cdc2 can transition to 0 or Cdc2 can degrade SK to 0. If Cdc2 changes first, SK remains at 1 and the cell cycle arrests. The hazard can be removed be reducing the weight of the inhibitory edge from Slp1 to Cdc2 and replacing constitutive Ste9 production with an activating edge from Slp1 to Ste9 [CITATION_3] .",
